                            <comment id="10523" author="sha0" created="Tue, 15 Mar 2016 17:28:59 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I have an interest in getting Perfect apps to be easily deployed with Heroku.  If I were to dive into that, would the Perfect community be available for dialogue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10524" author="seanstephens" created="Sat, 19 Mar 2016 16:10:09 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Check here as well: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/kylef/Curassow-example-helloworld&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/kylef/Curassow-example-helloworld&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10525" author="seanstephens" created="Mon, 28 Mar 2016 20:05:46 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks to Sha0, we now have a Heroku Buildpack in place: PerfectlySoft/Perfect-Heroku-Buildpack&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Sha0!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10526" author="sha0" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 00:37:03 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;An Ubuntu 15.10 Docker image with Swift and Perfect is now available: &lt;a href=&quot;https://hub.docker.com/r/perfectlysoft/ubuntu/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hub.docker.com/r/perfectlysoft/ubuntu/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10527" author="b20160" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2016 09:08:21 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;@Sha0 how do i use the Docker imgae&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10528" author="sha0" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2016 12:41:09 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello, b20160!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you click on the link, a Docker Hub web-page will appear.  On its lower right is a &quot;Docker Pull Command&quot; section.  This is how you can fetch the Docker image.  The image contains Ubuntu 15.10, Swift, and Perfect (including PerfectLib and PerfectServer).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once fetched, you can use Docker&apos;s &quot;run&quot; command to &quot;run&quot; the image: &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.docker.com/engine/userguide/containers/dockerizing/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://docs.docker.com/engine/userguide/containers/dockerizing/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Inside&quot; a running Perfect Docker, you can go into /usr/src/perfect/ and examine the Examples/ in there.  Or if you have your application available, you can fetch it into the Docker and try to build and run it!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10529" author="linxyfe" created="Sun, 12 Jun 2016 14:00:47 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;3) Docker&lt;br/&gt;
